==English==

===Etymology===
Probably from {{inh|en|enm|melsche}}, {{m|enm|molsh||soft}}, from {{inh|en|ang|melsc}}, {{m|ang|milisc||mellow; mild; sweet|lit=honeyed}}, probably from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*mili||honey}}. Compare {{cog|is|milska||a honeyed beverage}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/mʌltʃ/}}
* {{rhymes|en|ʌltʃ}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|es}}

# {{lb|en|agriculture|horticulture}} Any material used to cover the top [[layer]] of [[soil]] to protect, insulate, or decorate it, or to discourage [[weed]]s or retain [[moisture]].
#: ''An organic '''mulch''' is a '''mulch''' made of natural substances such as leaves or grass clippings.''
# {{lb|en|countable|agriculture}} A material used as mulch, as ''a decorative redwood bark mulch.''

